name: Pride and Poverty
description: An ancient moon mindful of what has been lost and left at the mercy of time which stands as incentive to the future heroism of the men of Scotland.  A shot from one of my trips to Scotland. What looks like the fragment of a stupendous ruin that in reality is popularly known as Scotland's folly ruins at the top of Calton Hill in Edinburgh. Built in memory of soldiers and sailors who died fighting in the Napoleonic Wars was left unfinished in 1829 due to the lack of funds.
